Our story takes place on an island-nation named Rollania. There the wise king ruled for many years, but his greedy twin sons were always anxious to inherit the kingdom. One day, a foreign surveyor came and informed them that the island was full of the rare metal expensivium. The two brothers were overcome with the promise of wealth, and arranged a tragic plumbing accident occur with their father.

In his will, they found he had left each son just 100 grams of expensivium, and that the island would be given to the son who could produce the most expensive statue of him 1 year after his death. And so, on the very day of his death the 2 sons start their fledgling enterprises on opposite ends of the island's deposit.